comment: L-Slash shows Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact from behind with Patterson's (TOR) hip, but it doesn't affect his RSBQ on his drive.

Drummond (DET) jumps vertically and turns slightly to absorb impact on Patterson's (TOR) play to the basket. While players may not turn in the air to defend a shot, they may turn slightly when absorbing impact. (See POE memo 3/31/14).
Tolliver (DET) makes contact with Patterson's (TOR) head on the layup attempt.
LATR shows that Vasquez (TOR) touches Jackson (DET) multiple times on the sides and back from behind, where he has no reasonable chance to legally defend his movement.
DeRozan (TOR) has his heel on the line of the restricted area when he takes the contact from Jackson (DET).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a blocking foul on DeRozan (TOR) was confirmed.
Vasquez (TOR) continues moving while he sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) without giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Jackson (DET) was overturned and Detroit was awarded possession.

Drummond (DET) jumps vertically and turns slightly to absorb impact on DeRozan's (TOR) play to the basket. While players may not turn in the air to defend a shot, they may turn slightly when absorbing impact. (See POE memo 3/31/14).
Patterson (TOR) uses his right arm to dislodge Drummond (DET) from behind while he is in the air and prevents him from securing the rebound.
Johnson (TOR) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Drummond (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he retreats and follows the path of DeRozan (TOR) on the drive to the basket.
Patterson (TOR) commits a take foul on Meeks (DET).
